@startuml akdb-postgres-request
title AKDB - PostgreSQL Request Path
actor Client
participant "CLI / API / MCP" as Surface
participant Service
participant "Database facade" as Facade
participant "SQL rewrite" as Rewrite
database PostgreSQL
Client -> Surface : operation
Surface -> Service : shared domain request
Service -> Facade : SQLite-compatible SQL + ? params
Facade -> Rewrite : rewrite JSON extraction and binds
Rewrite --> Facade : PostgreSQL SQL + %s params
Facade -> PostgreSQL : execute in transaction
PostgreSQL --> Facade : dict rows / rowcount
Facade --> Service : sqlite-compatible result
Service --> Client : domain response
note over Service,Facade
Domain services do not select a backend.
The same service tests run against SQLite and PostgreSQL.
end note
@enduml
